Canacol Climbs for Second Day in Bogota on Higher Crude Prices

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-04-20T17:29:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/canacol-climbs-for-second-day-in-bogota-on-higher-crude-prices.html
Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE) , the Calgary-
based  oil company  that operates fields in South America, rose
for a second day as crude oil climbed in New York on optimism
the economic recovery is accelerating.  Canacol advanced 3.8 percent to 2,470 pesos in Bogota
trading as of 1:06 p.m. New York Time, its biggest gain in a
month. The stock fell for 10 consecutive days through April 18,
and dipped to 2,320 pesos in intraday trading yesterday, its
lowest level since Sept. 30, on delayed results of drilling at
an exploratory well in Guyana.  “It’s a turnaround in a good environment in the stock
market,” said Santiago Melo, an analyst at Bogota-based
brokerage Alianza Valores SA.  Crude oil for June delivery climbed $3.29, or 3 percent, to
$111.57 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange . Futures
increased as much as $3.38 to $111.66, the biggest gain since
March 17. Prices are up 34 percent from a year ago.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  